				\begin{document} $$ \gamma = F_{s}/4+V_{i}+1-C/6   $$ \end{document}γ=Fs/4+Vi+1−C/6

where Vi is the number of vertices in the interior. They also show that 
10\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
